<h1>Tutorial &amp; Syntax help</h1>
<h2>Loops</h2>
<h3>1. If-Else:</h3>
<p>When ever you want to perform a set of operations based on a condition I=
F-ELSE is used.</p>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]"><span c=
lass=3D"hljs-keyword">if</span> conditional-expression
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#code</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">elif</span> conditional-expression
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#code</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">else</span>:
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#code</span>
</code></pre>
<h3>Note:</h3>
<p>Indentation is very important in Python, make sure the indentation is fo=
llowed correctly</p>
<h3>2. For:</h3>
<p>For loop is used to iterate over arrays(list, tuple, set, dictionary) or=
 strings.</p>
<h3>Example:</h3>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">mylist=
=3D(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Iphone"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"Pixel"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Samsung"</span>)
<span class=3D"hljs-keyword">for</span> i <span class=3D"hljs-keyword">in</=
span> mylist:
    <span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(i)
</code></pre>
<h3>3. While:</h3>
<p>While is also used to iterate a set of statements based on a condition. =
Usually while is preferred when number of iterations are not known in advan=
ce.</p>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]"><span c=
lass=3D"hljs-keyword">while</span> condition
    <span class=3D"hljs-comment">#code</span>
</code></pre>
<h2>Collections</h2>
<p>There are four types of collections in Python.</p>
<h3>1. List:</h3>
<p>List is a collection which is ordered and can be changed. Lists are spec=
ified in square brackets.</p>
<h3>Example:</h3>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">mylist=
=3D[<span class=3D"hljs-string">"iPhone"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"Pixel"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Samsung"</span>]
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(mylist)
</code></pre>
<h3>2. Tuple:</h3>
<p>Tuple is a collection which is ordered and can not be changed. Tuples ar=
e specified in round brackets.</p>
<h3>Example:</h3>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">myTuple=
=3D(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"iPhone"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"Pixel"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Samsung"</span>)
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(myTuple)
</code></pre>
<p>Below throws an error if you assign another value to tuple again.</p>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">myTuple=
=3D(<span class=3D"hljs-string">"iPhone"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"Pixel"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Samsung"</span>)
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(myTuple)
myTuple[<span class=3D"hljs-number">1</span>]=3D<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"onePlus"</span>
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(myTuple)
</code></pre>
<h3>3. Set:</h3>
<p>Set is a collection which is unordered and unindexed. Sets are specified=
 in curly brackets.</p>
<h3>Example:</h3>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">myset =
=3D {<span class=3D"hljs-string">"iPhone"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string=
">"Pixel"</span>,<span class=3D"hljs-string">"Samsung"</span>}
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(myset)
</code></pre>
<h3>4. Dictionary:</h3>
<p>Dictionary is a collection of key value pairs which is unordered, can be=
 changed, and indexed. They are written in curly brackets with key - value =
pairs.</p>
<h3>Example:</h3>
<pre style=3D"background-color:#f5f5f5;padding:12px;border-radius:4px;overf=
low-x:auto"><code class=3D"py hljs python" node=3D"[object Object]">mydict =
=3D {
    <span class=3D"hljs-string">"brand"</span> :<span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"iPhone"</span>,
    <span class=3D"hljs-string">"model"</span>: <span class=3D"hljs-string"=
>"iPhone 11"</span>
}
<span class=3D"hljs-built_in">print</span>(mydict)
</code></pre>
